  {
    "client_msg_id": "77e378b3-4609-40b7-ba97-eb55513775a0",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Vocally-transmitted music still carries words/syllables (e.g. canntaireachd <https://www.ubu.com/ethno/soundings/masters.html> as well as bol syllables etc), but adds the fluid expression of prosody. I don't see why programming languages can't have something similar, like a continuous channel of expression, without resorting to having to speak/sing it",
    "user": "URLP9FWR3",
    "ts": "1617716491.009800",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
